README
======

Dust Racing (Dustrac) is a tile-based, cross-platform 2D racing game written
in Qt (C++) and OpenGL.

Dust Racing comes with a Qt-based level editor for easy level creation.
A separate engine, MiniCore, is used for physics modeling.

License
-------

Dust Racing is licensed under GNU GPLv3. This applies to everything
in the source tree unless stated otherwise, including graphics.

See COPYING for the complete license text.

Source code
-----------

The source tree includes source code for the track editor and
the game itself. The game uses an 2D engine called MiniCore
written by Jussi Lind. The code is "documented" by using
Doxygen tags.

The source tree layout:

src/game/          : Source files for the game.
src/game/MiniCore/ : Source files for the graphics/physics engine.
src/editor/        : Source files for the track editor.
src/common/        : Shared files between the editor and the game.
data/              : Data mapping and configuration files.
data/images/       : Image files and textures.
data/images/raw/   : Some SVG-images used as the source for final images.
data/levels/       : Level data.
data/shaders/      : GLSL shaders.

See INSTALL for build and install instructions.

-- Jussi Lind <jussi.lind@iki.fi>

